                        <interp inst="t18720108-name-231" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LANE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Amhurst, pawnbroker, Edgware Road—this coat was pledged with us for 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18720108-name-232" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18720108-name-232" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18720108-name-232" type="surname" value="BUTTERFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18720108-name-232" type="given" value="EDWIN"></interp>EDWIN BUTTERFIELD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman S</hi> 3). I took the prisoner into custody on the 7th, and charged him with committing a burglary at No. 11, Belsize Road—he stated that the coat was given to him to pawn by a man whom he should not know at the corner of Earl Street, Lisson Grove, and he pawned it for 14<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—this was about 7 o'clock.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18720108-name-233" type="witnessName">
